    <p class="fs-16 m-t-20 text-master">
      We don’t give access to your personal information to any third-party services. We do reserve the right to disclose personal information when we believe that doing so is reasonably necessary to comply with the law or law enforcement, to prevent fraud or abuse, or to protect Hungryhead’s legal rights.
    </p>
</div>

 <div>
    <h3 class="m-t-30 semi-bold">What’s Public</h3>
    <p class="fs-16 m-t-20 text-master">
      Hungryhead is a private community and therefore, we don't share your content with search engines or third-party services. Only members who have joined the platform can see your profile, follow or message you through our services.
    </p>
</div>

<div>
  <h3 class="m-t-30 semi-bold">Members only</h3>
  <p class="fs-16 m-t-20 text-master">
    When you create an account, we create a profile page for you on Hungryhead, containing your username, name, profile information, and a list of ideas you have pitched. Whenever your name appears on Hungryhead (for instance, when you post comments, leave a feedback, make an investment, send messages, or contact us), people can click your account name to see your profile. The profile is searchable on Hungryhead, but not via search engines like Google. Here are some of the things that will be publicly viewable on your profile, or elsewhere on Hungryhead:
  </p>
  <ul class="fs-16 m-t-20 text-master">
    <li class="m-b-10">
      the name, username, school, college or university
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      any information you choose to add to your profile (like a picture, bio, interests, or your location)
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      ideas you've pitched
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      followers/followings you have
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      any comments or feedbacks you’ve posted on Hungryhead
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      any votes or virtual investments made
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div>
  <h3 class="m-t-30 semi-bold">How we use your personal data: </h3>
  <ul class="fs-16 m-t-20 text-master">
    <li class="m-b-10">
      identify you when you sign in to your account;
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      enable us to provide you with the Services;
    </li>
    <li class="m-b-10">
      send you marketing communications we think you may find useful, but only in accordance with your email preferences;
    </li>
